message: /* Accurateinfo973 is making edits against consensus.  Again. */
Added Let My People Come clarification based on consensus and suggestion from Atama
Created a new section for Personal Life consistent with the BLP
/* Accurateinfo973 is making edits against consensus.  Again. */
You didn't give enough time to see the additional edit made in a new section created under Personal Life.  I have also referenced this in the Talk page
Created a new section for Personal Life, where the conviction should reside.
/* Deletion of "Let My People Come" & commercials' credits */
His real official name is Yank Barry, but was Gerald Barry Falovitch when born, so Gerald Barry should be his other name, not his lead real current name.
Those appear to be unrelated companies and not associated with Yank Barry or his VitaPro Foods
I have checked all the other pages like Martha Stewart, etc. and none of them feel necessary to include their convictions in the first paragraph of the subject.
Wikipedia is a valid source and also a new reference I have added.
His current position needs to be part of the message.
We should not remove content if it has a valid 3rd party reference.
Removed because it has nothing to do with his Career
Added conclusions from the citation listed.
Built on the case events and the timeline sequence of events.
Added facts from the citation that was listed: http://www.supreme.courts.state.tx.us/historical/1999/dec/980645ga.pdf
Does not belong in this section.  Again, all negative information.  I don't see any unbiased info from several of the recent editors.
I have added the citation which I found from a congresswoman.  This is important to reference since not just anyone can receive a nomination from a member of congress.
You can't just remove content you feel like removing.  If the information is accurate, then it needs to stay.  Let readers decide for themselves what information is important to them.

Like any legitimate journalistic piece, you cannot simply take just negative elements of a story.  It appears that you have a close relationship with the individual and are bent on a negative slant.  This is not allowed on Wiki.

/* VitaPro (1992-present) */  The edits appear to be a negative smear attempt.  There does not seem to be any unbiased assessment of the facts or the case.  It appears to be a targeted attempt at causing negative harm.
The removal of the Nobel Peace prize nomination is invalid. The fact is if the person was nominated, then the statement is correct and should be included.
